1. Update current system
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt dist-upgrade -y

2. Install update-manager-core
sudo apt install update-manager-core -y

Ensure this line exists in your config: grep Prompt /etc/update-manager/release-upgrades
If it shows Prompt=lts, you're good.

3. Start the upgrade process
sudo do-release-upgrade
ğŸŸ¡ If it says â€œNo new release foundâ€, use:
sudo do-release-upgrade -d

5. Reboot after upgrade
sudo reboot

RECOMENDED way: SERIAL CONSOLE--'sudo -i'-- do-release-upgrade

Verify upgrade: lsb_release -a
